  "texts": [
    "Pollsters too have incentives to use them, to protect themselves against potential litigation and to show concern for deontological practices to enhance reputation.",
    "To the extent that pollsters may not be trusted to behave responsibly on this matter, they can be constrained with regulations, such as GDPR.",
    "New privacy regulations can require pollsters to adopt practices such as differential privacy and generative AI.",
    "Besides the mass extraction and storage of data, another new privacy-related worry has to do with the release of granular predictions about citizens' preferences.",
    "The polling industry currently publishes predictions at the constituency level."
